Detailed Description

FaceOutputDataV2 is a container for a set of facial landmark locations and an optional face-texture.

Facial landmarks are referenced by an integer value. They are defined in 3D coordinates (meters) with respect to the head-reference frame, and 2D normalised coordinates with respect to the face texture.

The head-reference frame is right-handed, has the origin at the midpoint between the eyeball centres, Z axis pointing into the head opposite the direction of the nose, Y axis pointing up through top of the head, and X axis pointing towards the right eye.

See also:
Facial Landmark Standard (FLM Standard) for a mapping of landmark index to facial location.
Note:
Do not inherit this class.
